      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-4">
        <li>✅ <strong>Multi-tier subscriptions:</strong> Creators can offer 3 price tiers (Basic/Premium/VIP)</li>
        <li>✅ <strong>Better creator tools:</strong> More granular privacy controls, scheduling</li>
        <li>✅ <strong>Follow-for-free option:</strong> Creators can build audience before paywall</li>
        <li>✅ <strong>Referral program:</strong> Creators earn from referring other creators</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 mt-6">Weaknesses:</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-4">
        <li>❌ <strong>Smaller user base:</strong> Less traffic than OnlyFans</li>
        <li>❌ <strong>Same 20% fee:</strong> No cost savings over OnlyFans</li>
        <li>❌ <strong>Less brand recognition:</strong> Harder to attract new subscribers</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 mb-6">
        <p class="font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">🎯 Best Use Case:</p>
        <p class="text-blue-800 text-sm">If you want more control over pricing tiers and don't mind a smaller audience, Fansly offers superior creator features. Many creators run both platforms simultaneously.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
